Text: I'm a little low on bandwidth right now, but I am seeding. When my other torrent gets other seeders, I'll concentrate on seeding only this one.

I changed the seeding rule to normal seeding, since superseeding in Vuze seems to upload bits in order from the beginning. It occurred to me that some of you might want to grab episodes one at the time out of order. And in superseeding no individual episodes would be available until all the bits are well seeded, which could take a couple of weeks with my upload speed.

From now on, I can upload about 8 Gigabytes a day of this torrent. I'm planning to leave my computer on during my Xmas vacation trip, so if there won't be any power outages here, this should be seeded non-stop until next year.
